%% 3.1.14 Wallet Management — sequence (layered)
%% Actor > UI > Controller > Service > Repository > Database

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Actor as Admin
    participant UI as UI (/wallets)
    participant WC as Controller (WalletController)
    participant WS as Service (WalletService)
    participant Repo as Repository (Wallet TransactionLog User)
    participant DB as Database (SQL Server)

    Actor->>UI: Open Wallet Management
    Actor->>UI: Search by guardian name or email

    UI->>WC: GET /api/Wallet/Search?keyword=...
    WC->>WS: SearchAsync
    WS->>Repo: Query wallets + user
    Repo->>DB: SELECT
    WS-->>WC: paged wallets (ID, UserId, name, email, balance)
    WC-->>UI: 200 — table row

    Actor->>UI: Click Xem — view history
    UI->>UI: Modal overlay — Lịch sử giao dịch ví

    UI->>WC: GET /api/Wallet/TransactionHistory/{walletId}?fromDate&toDate&method&status&...
    WC->>WS: GetTransactionHistoryAsync
    WS->>Repo: Query TransactionLog by wallet + filters
    Repo->>DB: SELECT
    WS-->>WC: history rows (before/after balance, amount, status, code)
    WC-->>UI: 200 — modal table read-only

    Note over Actor,DB: BR14 — không chỉnh sửa dòng lịch sử trong modal; nguồn dữ liệu cùng schema với Transactions ledger.
